    &lt;Title&gt;SAU and Jasmine Ward&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Gill&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Spent a couple of days in SAU and the nursing staff and Doctors were wonderful. Then moved to Jasmine ward for another day and again the nursing staff were outstanding. The nursing staff took time to explain things for me and were very supportive.
One thing that does seem to be a problem is that the Dr's don't properly update the notes. So move to a new ward and you have to start again with another Dr. I have found this problem several times before when my mother was in hsp. That should be improved. 
It goes without saying that there is a lot of waiting, but with my case in particular I don't think that could be avoided.  Staff kept me updated and explained what was happening. I'm very grateful for my treatment. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
